The paper deals with the problem of minimum bisection on planar graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are all likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves approximation algorithms and complexity analysis, which are topics in theoretical computer science, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) also likely sub-categories.
